An idea needs a well made bed to be its foundation before it can go anywhere.

textDelta: Ideas might seem valuable to the person who owns them, but only the grown flower appeals to outsiders
Scavengers might feed off of your ideas before they can bloom
An idea may be vulnerable and weak at first, but it could grow to be solid and hardy
As in the bottom of the food chain, at the basic level, all activity ultimately depends upon ideas to thrive.
